Prague Stock Exchange has fallen to a negative at the end of trade
After the early fall in the morning, the Prague Stock Exchange corrected losses.
CEZ transactions have reached almost half of the day-to-day trade.
The Prague Stock Exchange has been following up on its Monday fall since the start of Tuesday’s trade, when it fell by almost six percent.
This time, a drop in shares in Wall Street is behind the decline.
In our case, the market response to the result of the US House vote, which refused to support the plan for stabilising the financial sector.
The Fall of Stocks in Asia
Dramatic fall on Tuesdays experienced stock exchanges in Asia, although the indexes finally erased some of the losses during the day.
The Hang Seng Stock Exchange Index in Hong Kong wrote off almost four percent in the course of trading, but later deleted some of the losses and decreased to about 2.5 percent.
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index, which monitors the movement of Chinese stock on the Hong Kong stock exchange, has dropped by 3.8 percent, in Shanghai the markets have been closed.
Stocks on the Sydney Stock Exchange lost more than five percent, but eventually the losses decreased to 4.3 percent.
The storm in Taiwan, according to the local index, dropped 3.6 percent.
"The timing of the rescue action in the US is uncertain and will affect the financial markets around the world," said Joseph Yam, head of the Hong Kong Monetary Office.
Hong Kong, although part of China, sets its own monetary policy, regardless of the Chinese central bank.
The interest rates have Hong Kong at the same level as the United States.
According to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, American legislators should quickly return to the negotiations and the proposal to support the financial system.
Otherwise, it is said that other countries are likely to feel the impact.
The Blood Bath of American Stocks
On Monday, the American House of Representatives rejected a plan to support the financial system, which was to be spent up to 700 billion dollars (almost 12 trillion CZK).
The legislators ignored President George Bush's call to support the plan.
According to Bush, the plan would address the underlying causes of the financial crisis and help stabilise the economy as a whole.
American stocks experienced a bloodbath on Monday, and the major stock indices experienced the biggest fall in more than 20 years.
The Dow Jones Index dropped by almost seven percent, and to a similar extent it was last seen in 1987.
The index had fallen before the vote, but as soon as it turned out that the proposal had not passed, the index was in a free fall.
The U.S. government can pump $700 billion into banks
The Supreme Representatives of the US Congress and the Government of President George W. Bush agreed on a broader form of an agreement on financial assistance to the US financial system.
It will be voted on at the beginning of next week.
American legislators have made a breakthrough in the discussions on the approval of the rescue plan in the form of financial assistance to the US financial system of 700 billion dollars (approximately 12 trillion crowns).
But it's not won yet.
Congressmen have to complete some of the details of the agreement before they can publish and vote on the final form of the law.
The financial system support plan will be discussed in the House of Representatives on Monday.
On Sunday, Reuters was told by the chairman of the Committee on Banking and Financial Services, Barney Frank.
According to sources, the Senate could vote on the plan first on Wednesday.
According to economists, the notification of the approval of the rescue plan should be the first significant psychological factor for the recovery of the financial markets.
But then there will be "sobriety" thanks to the complexity of the mechanisms that help the markets to achieve in practice.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
"We made great progress.
We have solved our different views on what the market stabilisation package is supposed to look like," said Democrat Nancy Pelosi for Bloomberg.
According to her, the final vote could still take place on Sunday.
The legislators met with the US Treasury Minister Henry Paulson on Sunday night to give a definitive form to the government fund.
This should buy out non-sale mortgage assets from financial companies that download financial companies into severe losses and threaten the stability of the entire system.
"We are on the verge of a definitive agreement on a plan that will work and must also be effective on the market.
There is still a need to continue the recovery plan, but I think we are there," Paulson said.
Asian trade signal
The global financial crisis is affecting stock markets that are falling sharply.
According to Nevada’s democratic Senator Harry Reid, legislators are trying to reach a definitive agreement in Congress on Sunday.
They want to calm investors down before trading in Asian financial markets, which are the first in the time zone where Congress’s decision could affect Monday’s trade.
It is not yet clear, however, when the two chambers of the U.S. Congress will vote on the law, or whether they can't get caught up in a problem at the last minute.
The legislators hope to be approved in the next few days.
But the law will still see a number of changes.
The total amount allocated to the aid scheme shall be divided into two parts.
The initial $ 350 billion is to be available as soon as possible, as requested by President George Bush.
But Congress can block the release of the remaining amount if it feels that the program is not doing its job, followed by another $100 billion and later the ultimate $ 350 billion.
Bush appreciated progress in the negotiations
Although the President may veto this decision, Congress may overrule its veto.
Despite these changes, however, the basic idea of the programme, which was to obtain funding for the redemption of bad mortgage securities, the value of which has fallen because hundreds of thousands of Americans are unable to repay their mortgages, has been preserved.
"We've worked everything out.
The House of Representatives should be able to vote on the bill on Sunday and the Senate on Monday," said Republican Senator Judd Gregg.
US President Bush is also pleased with the progress in the negotiations.
His spokesman Tony Fratto stated that Bush is satisfied with Saturday's progress and appreciates the "bottom-up effort to stabilise our financial markets and protect our economy".
Limitation of golden parachutes
The Chairman of the Senate’s Banking Committee, Christopher Dodd, the head of the negotiator, said that the legislators had agreed on the responsibility for the cash programme, protection of the taxpayers from losses, closure of the relief, timing of the financing of the plan.
The new law is also intended to limit the so-called golden parachutes for directors of companies participating in the programme and set up a committee to supervise the fund.
It should be run by the Ministry of Finance.
"We have worked very hard on this and have made great progress towards an agreement that will work and be useful for the market and for all Americans," Paulson said.
The plan also includes help for homeowners who have trouble paying back.
The government should negotiate new instalments for the mortgages it buys in order to reduce the monthly cost of repayments to debtors and allow them to keep their homes.
Marek: Psychological assistance
The proposed plan is a good idea, according to the chief economist Patri Finance David Mark, but it will be very difficult to implement.
"And that's because they don't know what mechanism and at what cost problem assets are going to be bought out.
This will be decisive for how the financial sector and the government share their losses," Marek said this week for the server iHNed.cz.
If the plan is approved now or at the beginning of next week, it's not that important, according to Mark.
"It is much more important that this week's congressmen agree that they support this plan and that it will be sacrificed as soon as possible.
The psychological importance of the agreement on approval is at this moment the most important," Marek stressed.
Knife blade fight: MP3 players against mobile phones.
We can help you choose
While almost every cell phone can play MP3 files, no MP3 player can make a phone call.
From that, it seems clear that it's better to buy a phone.
Yet, there are enough reasons to buy a separate player.
The choice depends entirely on the way in which the future owner is used and the requirements.
You may find it hard to get a high-end, expensive turntable home to listen to Maxim Turbulenc's latest album.
However, such music products do not appear on LP boards and there is no qualitative reason for that.
However, if your shelves are guilty of art rock, jazz or blues, you are likely to dream of such a turntable.
