This service could already be a strong argument in itself for the acquisition of a music cell.
Unfortunately, the offer of operators is lousy and is usually limited to high-speed radio hits.
The prices are not the lowest either.
However, it is generally assumed that this particular way of selling music (whether via GSM, Internet or wireless Internet) will take control of the music industry in the future.
Most people carry their phones around all the time.
Whenever you get a desire to hear something, you can feel your phone in your pocket while the MP3 player is lying forgotten at home.
However, it still depends on whether you always carry headphones or at least wire handsfree.
If not, you can use an integrated speaker, which has almost every cell phone, but only a minimum of MP3 players.
Perhaps the biggest advantage of music phones will be for many.
